/******************* To generate the file you need for OTA *******************/
1. In the Arduino IDE, go to the top menu and select Sketch.

2. Click on Export Compiled Binary (or press Ctrl + Alt + S).

3. The IDE will compile the code again. Watch the progress bar at the bottom.

4. Once it says "Done compiling", go to Sketch > Show Sketch Folder.

5. You should now see a folder named build or a file directly in the folder ending in .bin.(OTA.ino.bin)

6. Can use that single .bin file to update 100 client devices in the web
	Web Browser : Access"IP/update" >> Login"credentials (User / Pass123)" >> Flash"Select new .bin file and click Upload" 
